The paper deals with the problem of designing efficient partition oracles for graphs with excluded minors, which is a topic in graph theory and combinatorics. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as likely sub-categories. The paper's focus on graph properties and approximation algorithms suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's relevance to planarity testing suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as a possible sub-category.
